好了 Albert
All right, Albert,

24
00:04:17,339 --> 00:04:19,556
回你的"造船室"吧
you go into your boat building.

25
00:04:19,635 --> 00:04:22,895
你需要什么 先生?
Now, sir, what do you require?

26
00:04:22,974 --> 00:04:25,050
是只过一个晚上呢
Is it a room for the night,

27
00:04:25,131 --> 00:04:26,821
还是长住?
or for a longer stay?

28
00:04:33,378 --> 00:04:34,866
这么说吧 Warren太太
Well, Mrs. Warren,

29
00:04:34,943 --> 00:04:39,111
我看不出有什么特别的理由 让你觉得不安
I cannot think you have any particular reason for uneasiness

30
00:04:39,684 --> 00:04:43,596
你也注意到了我还有其他事要忙
and you note I have other things to engage me.

31
00:04:43,675 --> 00:04:46,000
福尔摩斯 一个房客
Holmes, the matter of a lodger

32
00:04:46,076 --> 00:04:48,993
在他的房间里待上一个星期也不露面
remaining unseen in his room for more than a week

33
00:04:49,068 --> 00:04:51,606
难免引人好奇
is surely of some passing interest.

34
00:04:51,678 --> 00:04:54,718
换了是我 房东几个星期也不会看到我
If I were a lodger she wouldn't see me for weeks on end.

35
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,416
这没有让你不安吧 Hudson太太?
That doesn't trouble you, does it Mrs. Hudson?

36
00:04:57,488 --> 00:04:58,478
我没什么不安的
Nothing troubles me

37
00:04:58,515 --> 00:05:00,618
只要是有你 福尔摩斯先生
where you're concerned, Mr. Holmes.

38
00:05:00,689 --> 00:05:02,427
但你还记得么
But if you remember

39
00:05:02,464 --> 00:05:06,385
一年前 你就接过Warren太太的 一个房客的案子
you arranged an affair for a lodger of Mrs. Warren's a year ago.

40
00:05:06,422 --> 00:05:08,087
是的 你接过 先生
Yes, you did, sir,

41
00:05:08,124 --> 00:05:10,951
一个意大利绅士 Firmani先生
an Italian gentleman, Mr. Firmani.

42
00:05:12,522 --> 00:05:14,135
Enrico Firmani
Enrico Firmani.

43
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:21,134
Firmani先生不厌其烦地 说着你的好 先生
Mr. Firmani never stopped talking of your kindness, sir.

44
00:05:21,171 --> 00:05:24,482
你怎么样打破黑暗带来光明
How you brought light into the darkness.

45
00:05:26,608 --> 00:05:28,985
那是个瓦格纳之夜
It was a Wagner night I think.

46
00:05:32,001 --> 00:05:34,314
让我们听听这个房客的事吧
Let us hear about this lodger.

47
00:05:40,523 --> 00:05:42,599
它吓着我了 福尔摩斯先生
It frightens me, Mr. Holmes.

48
00:05:42,681 --> 00:05:44,828
吓的我没法睡觉
I can't sleep for fright

49
00:05:44,908 --> 00:05:48,348
听着他的脚步声从这到那
hearing his footsteps moving here and moving there

50
00:05:48,422 --> 00:05:50,889
从早到晚一刻不停
from early morning to late at night

51
00:05:50,961 --> 00:05:53,632
却从来见不到他 哪怕是一眼
and I never, never catch so much as a glimpse of him.

52
00:05:54,090 --> 00:05:56,869
Warren先生也像我一样紧张
Mr. Warren is as nervous as I am.

53
00:06:01,816 --> 00:06:04,442
那家伙在逃避什么呢 福尔摩斯先生?
What's the fellow hiding from, Mr. Holmes?

54
00:06:05,052 --> 00:06:05,956
他干过什么?
What has he done?

55
00:06:05,993 --> 00:06:07,978
你知道除了那个女仆
You see except for the maid

56
00:06:08,014 --> 00:06:10,304
家里就剩下她跟那个房客了
she's all alone in the house with him.

57
00:06:10,375 --> 00:06:12,391
不 我受不了了
No, I can't stand it.

58
00:06:12,463 --> 00:06:13,599
我的神经承受不住了
My, nerves can't stand it.

59
00:06:13,636 --> 00:06:15,434
华生 看看怎么回事
Watson, cope.

60
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,273
Hudson太太 拿嗅盐来 要是你有的话
Smelling salts, Mrs. Hudson, if you have them.

61
00:06:28,850 --> 00:06:31,032
仔细想想 Warren太太
Take time to consider, Mrs. Warren,

62
00:06:31,111 --> 00:06:34,742
最微小的事也可能是最重要的
the smallest point may be the most essential.

63
00:06:40,435 --> 00:06:42,831
他是10天前来的
He came 10 days ago

64
00:06:42,905 --> 00:06:44,921
他向我房租
and he asked me my terms

65
00:06:44,993 --> 00:06:47,662
我就说一星期12先令
so I told him 12 shillings a week.

66
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:49,817
一间小的起居室和卧室
There's a small sitting room and a bedroom

67
00:06:49,899 --> 00:06:52,152
位于顶楼 里面一切齐备
all complete all at the top of the house

68
00:06:52,229 --> 00:06:56,045
他说愿意付一星期3镑
and he said he'd pay me three pounds a week for it.

69
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:57,596
3镑?
Three pounds?

70
00:06:57,633 --> 00:06:59,392
是的 先生 一星期3镑
Yes, sir, three pounds a week

71
00:06:59,428 --> 00:07:01,471
但是得遵守他的条件
as long as I kept his terms.

72
00:07:01,509 --> 00:07:02,823
什么条件?
What terms?

73
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:05,441
嗯 他想要一把房屋的钥匙
Well, he wanted a key to the house.

74
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:07,807
这没什么 大多数房客都有
That's all right most of my lodgers have them

75
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:12,119
但他要求完全一个人
but he was to be left entirely to himself

76
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:15,746
决不能被打扰
and never on any account to be disturbed.

77
00:07:15,818 --> 00:07:18,415
这也没什么奇怪的
Well, there's nothing very wonderful about that.

78
00:07:18,496 --> 00:07:20,968
算不上个理由 可这又是根本没有道理的
Well, not in reason but this is out of all reason.

79
00:07:21,311 --> 00:07:22,801
他住进来有10天了
He's been in there 10 days

80
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,195
不管是早晨 中午还是晚上
morning, noon and night

81
00:07:24,272 --> 00:07:26,039
不论是她 还是Warren先生或女仆
and neither she nor Mr. Warren

82
00:07:26,116 --> 00:07:28,298
都没有看过他 哪怕就一眼
nor the maid has once set eyes on him.

83
00:07:28,377 --> 00:07:29,558
除了刚来的那个晚上
And apart from the first night,

84
00:07:29,595 --> 00:07:32,159
他也从来没有出去过
he's never once gone out.

85
00:07:32,448 --> 00:07:33,543
哦 刚来的晚上他出去过么?
Oh, he did go out on the first night?

86
00:07:33,581 --> 00:07:34,830
是的 出去过
Oh, yes, he did,

87
00:07:34,866 --> 00:07:36,620
他很晚才回来
he returned very late,

88
00:07:37,128 --> 00:07:38,166
我已经睡觉了
I'd gone to bed

89
00:07:38,203 --> 00:07:40,115
是Warren先生看到他的
but Mr. Warren saw him.

90
00:07:40,152 --> 00:07:42,683
他回来时已经过了午夜
It was after midnight he'd come back.

91
00:07:47,659 --> 00:07:51,056
那吃饭怎么办 我肯定他得吃东西
These meals, I mean surely he eats.

92
00:07:51,093 --> 00:07:52,882
他要吃饭时就摇铃
Well he rings when he wants them.

93
00:07:52,918 --> 00:07:55,085
我们把饭放在他门口的椅子上
We put them on a chair outside his door.

94
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:57,420
要是他还需要些什么的话
If he wants anything else

95
00:07:57,498 --> 00:08:00,436
他就写在一小片纸上
he writes it on a bit of paper,

96
00:08:01,389 --> 00:08:05,898
用铅笔写
this just in pencil,

97
00:08:06,056 --> 00:08:08,594
只有只言片语
just the one word nothing more.

98
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:09,911
你看看
Here.

99
00:08:13,641 --> 00:08:18,747
早饭时女仆把"每日新闻"报带给他
The maid leaves the Daily Chronicle with him every morning at breakfast.

100
00:08:20,321 --> 00:08:21,945
为什么用印刷体来写?
Why is it printed?

101
00:08:22,026 --> 00:08:24,564
为了隐瞒他的笔迹
Well, to conceal his handwriting.

102
00:08:24,635 --> 00:08:26,224
华生 你有什么推论
Watson, deduce.

103
00:08:26,305 --> 00:08:28,522
我?
Me?

104
00:08:28,601 --> 00:08:35,163
铅笔尖很宽 写起来带点紫色
Well, the pencil is broad tipped and violet tinted.

105
00:08:35,664 --> 00:08:38,962
写的时候...写的时候相当用力
And it's used with, well it's used with considerable pressure

106
00:08:38,999 --> 00:08:42,308
还没写完纸就被划破了
and the paper's been torn off at the side before the printing was done.

107
00:08:42,345 --> 00:08:47,767
你能看到肥皂(soap)的这个S没写完
You can see the S of soap is partly gone.

108
00:08:47,804 --> 00:08:48,887
表明什么?
Suggesting?

109
00:08:48,923 --> 00:08:49,804
匆忙
Haste.

110
00:08:49,841 --> 00:08:51,139
或者是谨慎
Or caution.

111
00:08:51,668 --> 00:08:53,932
说说这个男人的年龄和长相
The man's age and appearance?

112
00:08:53,969 --> 00:08:57,033
他不到30 先生 一身黑衣服
Oh, he's under 30, sir, he's very dark,

113
00:08:57,071 --> 00:08:59,160
中等身材 胡子刮得很干净
middle height, clean-shaven.

114
00:08:59,197 --> 00:09:02,203
说话的口音和Firmani先生很像
Oh, has an accent like Mr. Firmani.

115
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:03,346
当然 他没有名字?
Of course no name?

116
00:09:03,427 --> 00:09:04,706
没有 先生
No, sir.

117
00:09:06,036 --> 00:09:07,351
没有信件或者访客
No letters or callers.

118
00:09:07,428 --> 00:09:08,155
一个都没有 先生
None, sir.

119
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:09,441
他的行李呢?
His luggage?

120
00:09:09,968 --> 00:09:10,999
上面有没有签条?
Labels?

121
00:09:11,082 --> 00:09:12,327
或者贴纸?
Stickers?

122
00:09:14,352 --> 00:09:16,243
"白色之星"号
White Star.

123
00:09:17,518 --> 00:09:18,869
十天前
Ten days ago.

124
00:09:21,623 --> 00:09:23,390
从纽约来
New York.

125
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:29,196
我想我们还是等等
I think that we must wait

126
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:33,476
直到有更多的线索
until we have a little more material.

127
00:09:33,556 --> 00:09:35,335
二位请便吧
Please vanish both of you.

128
00:09:36,619 --> 00:09:37,763
谢谢
Thank you.

129
00:09:40,758 --> 00:09:42,692
谢谢你 福尔摩斯先生
Thank you, Mr. Holmes.

130
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:44,511
噢 谢谢你 医生
Oh, thank you, Doctor.

131
00:09:46,882 --> 00:09:48,997
交给我吧 Hudson太太
Leave it to me, Mrs. Hudson.

132
00:09:59,371 --> 00:10:02,504
你得承认 福尔摩斯 这事还是有点意思的
You must admit, Holmes, there are some points of interest.

133
00:10:03,581 --> 00:10:05,052
只有一点 房间里的人
Only that the man in the rooms

134
00:10:05,089 --> 00:10:07,396
可能和订房间的人不是同一个人了
may not be the one who engaged them.

135
00:10:08,035 --> 00:10:09,940
对啊 当然 我怎么没有想到这一点
Yes, of course, I hadn't thought of that.

136
00:10:10,262 --> 00:10:12,700
在订了房间后他立刻就走了
And he went out immediately after taking the rooms

137
00:10:12,738 --> 00:10:14,393
直到午夜才回来
and returned at midnight.

138
00:10:15,237 --> 00:10:16,837
为什么要换人呢?
Why a substitution?

139
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:21,319
值得为此
Well, opens up a pleasurable feel

140
00:10:21,395 --> 00:10:24,064
展开一番推理
for intelligent speculation

141
00:10:24,143 --> 00:10:26,360
有一条调查的线索
and there is one line of investigation.

142
00:10:26,439 --> 00:10:29,808
Warren太太的前房客
Mrs. Warren's former lodger.

143
00:10:29,884 --> 00:10:34,296
那不勒斯的Enrico Firmani
Enrico Firmani of Naples.

144
00:10:34,372 --> 00:10:37,775
他在皇家歌剧院的后台工作
He works backstage at the Royal Opera House.

145
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:45,988
我曾帮他找到过失散的至亲
I helped him find a close relative once.

146
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:48,114
很简单的案子
A simple matter.

147
00:10:48,184 --> 00:10:50,472
Catchpole街37号
37 Catchpole Street.

148
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:52,732
你补充了些东西?
You added something?

149
00:10:52,812 --> 00:10:55,516
对那些需要帮助的同乡来说 他是一个朋友
A friend to his fellow countrymen in need.

150
00:10:55,594 --> 00:10:56,910
你是不是认为
Do you suppose

151
00:10:56,986 --> 00:10:58,610
他向他需要帮助的同乡
he could've recommended his former lodgings

152
00:10:58,691 --> 00:11:00,220
推荐了他的前房东?
to a fellow countryman in need?

153
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:01,843
很有可能
Possibly.

154
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:06,143
但这解释不了房客的举动
Well, it doesn't explain the lodge's behavior.

155
00:11:07,806 --> 00:11:09,354
举动?
Behavior?

156
00:11:09,894 --> 00:11:11,838
什么举动?
What behavior?

157
00:11:15,459 --> 00:11:17,747
你怎么知道这儿的?
How do you know this address?

158
00:11:17,825 --> 00:11:20,494
从福尔摩斯先生那里
Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

159
00:11:20,574 --> 00:11:22,756
福尔摩斯先生?
Mr. Holmes?

160
00:11:22,836 --> 00:11:26,382
他总是保留着他过去委托人的相关记录
He always keeps a record of his past clients.

161
00:11:26,454 --> 00:11:28,292
要是福尔摩斯要问我的话
But if Holmes has something to ask

162
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:29,956
为什么他不亲自来
why does he not come himself,

163
00:11:30,038 --> 00:11:32,114
为什么派你来 华生医生?
why send you, Dr. Watson?

164
00:11:32,195 --> 00:11:36,749
我偶尔也自己行动
Well, I do on occasion act for myself.

165
00:11:36,822 --> 00:11:40,190
恐怕我帮不了你
Well, I cannot help you I'm afraid.

166
00:11:40,266 --> 00:11:43,421
我对Warren太太的这个房客一无所知
I know nothing of this lodger of Mrs. Warren's.

167
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:45,827
他是不是你的一个同乡
Is he perhaps a fellow countryman of yours

168
00:11:45,902 --> 00:11:48,927
刚从美国来 需要帮助?
recently arrived from America in need of help?

169
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:51,108
那你告诉福尔摩斯我就在这里 如果他需要我的话
Then tell him I'm here if he needs me.

170
00:11:52,095 --> 00:11:53,561
只能说这么多了
That is all I can say.

171
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,233
失陪了
Excuse me,

172
00:11:56,265 --> 00:11:58,521
<i>("纽约时报" 意大利商人命丧布鲁克林)</i>
The New Nork

173
00:11:56,508 --> 00:11:57,942
现在我得去工作了
I must go to work now.

174
00:11:59,262 --> 00:12:01,894
可能是Warren太太需要帮助
It may be that Mrs. Warren needs help.

175
00:12:01,976 --> 00:12:03,743
这个男人在打扰她的家庭
The man is disturbing her household.

176
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:06,737
为什么 他做了什么了?
Why, what does he do to them?

177
00:12:06,813 --> 00:12:08,149
这个案子更主要是关于他没有做什么
Well, it's more a case of what he doesn't do.

178
00:12:08,186 --> 00:12:10,035
他从早到晚从不露面
He doesn't appear from dawn till dusk.

179
00:12:10,117 --> 00:12:12,495
他的饮食留在门外
He has his meals on a tray left outside the door.

180
00:12:13,423 --> 00:12:14,952
如果他是一个亡命之徒
If he's a fugitive from justice

181
00:12:15,022 --> 00:12:17,025
我们应该把他交给警察
we should turn him over to the police.

182
00:12:17,597 --> 00:12:18,825
警察?
Police?

183
00:12:19,998 --> 00:12:22,296
不 不
No, no.

184
00:12:25,043 --> 00:12:26,549
再见 妈妈
Caio Mama.

185
00:12:35,758 --> 00:12:37,299
如果有什么问题的话
If there is a problem,

186
